begin_memory_text: She asked me a lot of questions about where I was from and I told her a little bit about me and she told me that she was from Chicago and that's all I really remember about the beginning.
middle_memory_text: In the middle of the conversation, I know that we talked a little bit more about my experiences and possibly moving to Europe. I know that we also talked a lot about COVID and what things were like for each of us.
end_memory_text: I think towards the end of the conversation we were talking mostly about Trump and how we were both liberal and we both don't really like Biden but we hope that he gets elected because it's embarrassing the way Trump is running the country into the ground.
rest_of_day_open: Right now I think that I will do a few more of these if I can do them. I also work as a tutor so I'm going to be tutoring a lot more sessions for the rest of the week. I'm also going to try to eat healthier this week.
critical_positive: I think that the conversation worked because we both had the same views about politics and we both saw Trump in the same way, as a sort of crazy uncle. If we held different political views, I don't think that the conversation would have worked but I was surprised she asked about it, to be honest.
critical_negative: I think that it didn't really work because there were a lot of pauses. The woman I was speaking with asked a lot of questions for me to answer and it felt a little bit awkward, like I was giving a job interview, but I'm a people person so I didn't mind answering them but I did feel a bit uncomfortable.

begin_memory_text: I asked her where she was from and where she was.She asked me where I was and how daily life was affected here.  We started talking about Covid and how it affected us individually. It was a very bland forced conversation.
middle_memory_text: We talked about daily life during Covid, She told me about her school and how teaching is where she is at, I told her a bit about where we are in the Covid process.
end_memory_text: We talked about the election and mostly about Trump. We discussed our political views and voting, what we believe and my thought that Trump is the crazy uncle from the family dinner  who now controls the country.
rest_of_day_open: I see it going peacefully.  I don't have many plans for the rest of the week so I expect it will be spent working and cleaning up after the roofers who are now making a mess of my yard. I don't have much to say about the upcoming week. That's it.
critical_positive: We both wanted to talk and fill up the space of time. We connected on politics at some points and those points are not difficult to connect on. We were open to talking and making the conversation function on a basic level even though there was nothing at all in common.
critical_negative: We had nothing in common and had to work to find common ground. Other than Covid and politics there would be nothing to discuss. Our educational and life experiences were so different and she didn't seem to have much curiousity about the world ina way I would have found compelling.
